main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright object moving very fast in the sky over Yellow Springs, Ohio in September 1965.
interesting points: The object was brighter than the star Polaris and moved very quickly.
The object had the same color as a star and appeared as a point of light.
The object disappeared over the horizon after being observed for about 5 minutes.
The report indicates the object was concluded to be the ECHO II satellite.
The observer was asked detailed questions about the sighting, including time of day, weather conditions, and characteristics of the object.
